<p><b>Carnivore</b> was a system implemented by the <a href="/wiki/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation" title="Federal Bureau of Investigation">Federal Bureau of Investigation</a> that was designed to monitor email and electronic communications. It used a customizable <a href="/wiki/Packet_sniffer" title="Packet sniffer" class="mw-redirect">packet sniffer</a> that can monitor all of a target user's Internet traffic. Carnivore was implemented during the <a href="/wiki/Presidency_of_Bill_Clinton" title="Presidency of Bill Clinton">Clinton administration</a> with the approval of the <a href="/wiki/Attorney_General" title="Attorney General" class="mw-redirect">Attorney General</a>.</p>
